<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-02-08T09:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-02-08T09:00:00-05:00" n="433" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d433">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">561.35E1/122: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Atherton</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-02-08T14:00:00+00:00">February
                                    8, 1936—2 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received February 8—10:35 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>53. Your 47, February 6, 2 p.m. According to reliable information the
                            rumor, which has likewise been current here, is believed to have
                            originated in the United States. A responsible and informed official of
                            the Colonial Office when questioned about it is reported to have made
                            the reply that the United States had not yet been officially consulted
                            about the conference and that he had no knowledge as to the source of
                            the rumor.</p>
                        <pb facs="0604" n="524" xml:id="pg_524"/>
                        <p>A meeting took place 2 days ago between British representatives and
                            Javanese. The British have not yet had time to reach any decision as a
                            result of this conference. Further information may be available early
                            next week.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Atherton</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>